 :tx/rationale "Create task: EPIC: Output-as-Observation — every knowledge-producing command embeds auto-observation datoms in its own transaction, eliminating 80% of manual braid observe ceremony (INV-STORE-014, INV-HARVEST-009, INV-GUIDANCE-014). BACKGROUND: The store comonad principle (Session 028): every store interaction IS an observation. Currently braid observe is a separate command costing ~3s + cognitive formulation effort. Agents skip it ~70% of the time (30 of 44 closes this session had no matching observation). The fix: the command output IS the observation. When braid task close writes its close transaction, it also writes an :auto-obs/* entity with the close reason as body, spec refs auto-parsed, graph neighbors auto-linked. Same transaction, zero extra IO. For task create: the title IS the observation. For transact: the rationale IS the observation. braid observe (explicit) remains for pure insights not triggered by commands. APPROACH: 4 tasks: auto_obs_datoms helper, wire into 4 command functions, P(t) metric, verification. ACCEPTANCE: (A) braid task close --reason 'X' produces :auto-obs/* datom in same tx. (B) No auto-obs for read commands (status, query, seed). (C) No auto-obs when command IS observe (avoid duplicates). (D) Auto-obs has :exploration/related-spec Refs to parsed spec entities. (E) P(t) appears in braid status alongside F(S). TRACES TO: INV-STORE-014, INV-HARVEST-009, INV-GUIDANCE-014, ADR-GUIDANCE-002."
